<div class="header">
  <div class="header-top">
    <div>
      <h1>Client Risk Monitor — Good News / Bad News</h1>
      <div class="subtitle">Cummings Electrical — Financial Risk Management &bull; 30-Day Lookback</div>
    </div>
    <div class="date-badge">Feb 3 – Mar 3, 2026</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <div class="grid">

    <!-- ===================== COREWEAVE ===================== -->
    <div class="company-card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <div>
          <div class="ticker">CRWV</div>
          <div class="company-name">CoreWeave, Inc.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="risk-badge risk-critical">&#9888; Critical</div>
      </div>

      <div class="toggle-bar">
        <div class="toggle-btn good-btn active" onclick="switchPanel(this,'crwv-good','crwv-bad')">
          <span class="icon">&#9650;</span> Good News <span class="count">5</span>
        </div>
        <div class="toggle-btn bad-btn" onclick="switchPanel(this,'crwv-bad','crwv-good')">
          <span class="icon">&#9660;</span> Bad News <span class="count">5</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="crwv-good" class="news-panel active">

        <a href="https://nvidianews.nvidia.com/news/nvidia-and-coreweave-strengthen-collaboration-to-accelerate-buildout-of-ai-factories" target="_blank" class="news-item good">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Jan 26, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag positive">Liquidity Boost</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">NVIDIA Invests $2B, Expands Strategic Partnership</div>
          <div class="news-impact">NVIDIA purchased CRWV Class A shares at $87.20/share, bringing its stake to ~11.5%. Partnership expanded to include next-gen Rubin chips, Vera CPUs, and a 5GW AI factory buildout target by 2030. NVIDIA backstop guarantees up to $6.3B in unused capacity through April 2032.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> NVIDIA Newsroom</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/coreweave-seeks-8-5-billion-201337551.html" target="_blank" class="news-item good">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Feb 24, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag positive">Funding Access</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">$8.5B Financing Secured by Meta Contracts</div>
          <div class="news-impact">Delayed-draw term loan backed by $14.2B Meta contract plus a previously undisclosed $5B+ agreement. Expected investment-grade rating due to Meta's credit profile. ~6% interest rate. Closing expected March 2026.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> Bloomberg via Yahoo Finance</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20260226281661/en/CoreWeave-Reports-Strong-Fourth-Quarter-and-Fiscal-Year-2025-Results" target="_blank" class="news-item good">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Feb 26, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag positive">Revenue Visibility</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">Revenue Backlog Grows to $66.8B</div>
          <div class="news-impact">Backlog up $11.2B sequentially from $55.6B in Q3. Weighted contract length extended to 5 years. New customer wins include CrowdStrike, Midjourney, Runway, Mercado Libre, Cursor, and Cognition.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> BusinessWire — Earnings Release</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/26/coreweave-crwv-q4-earnings-report-2025.html" target="_blank" class="news-item good">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Feb 26, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag positive">Execution</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">Q4 Revenue Beats Consensus, Up 110% YoY</div>
          <div class="news-impact">$1.57B revenue vs. $1.55B expected. Full-year 2025 revenue $5.1B, up 168% YoY. Previously disclosed construction delays resolved ahead of schedule. Revolver expanded to $2.5B.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> CNBC</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/02/27/coreweave-crwv-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript/" target="_blank" class="news-item good">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Feb 26, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag positive">Debt Structure</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">No Near-Term Debt Maturities Before 2029</div>
          <div class="news-impact">Only self-amortizing contract-backed and vendor financing debt maturing before 2029. Weighted average interest rate dropped 300bps in 2025. $2.6B convertible notes raised in Q4.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> Motley Fool — Earnings Transcript</span>
        </a>

      </div>

      <div id="crwv-bad" class="news-panel">

        <a href="https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/03/03/3248621/0/en/Kessler-Topaz-Meltzer-Check-LLP-CoreWeave-CRWV-Class-Action-Lawsuit-Investors-Face-March-13-2026-Deadline.html" target="_blank" class="news-item bad">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Feb 26, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag negative">Cash Burn</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">Q4 Net Loss of $452M — Nearly Double Expectations</div>
          <div class="news-impact">EPS of -$0.89 vs. -$0.49 expected — a 324% negative surprise. Adjusted EBITDA of $898M also missed $929M consensus. Interest expense hit $388M in Q4 alone, up from $149M the prior year.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> GlobeNewswire — Hagens Berman</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/26/coreweave-crwv-q4-earnings-report-2025.html" target="_blank" class="news-item bad">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Feb 26, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag negative">Margin Squeeze</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">Q1 2026 Revenue Guidance Misses by ~15%</div>
          <div class="news-impact">Guided $1.9B–$2.0B vs. $2.29B consensus. Margins expected at low single digits in Q1, expanding to low double digits only by Q4. Q1 interest expense guided at $510M–$590M. Stock fell ~20%.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> CNBC</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://investorplace.com/2026/03/coreweave-stock-crwv-buy-the-dip/" target="_blank" class="news-item bad">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Feb 26, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag negative">Leverage Risk</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">Capital Intensity Far Exceeds Expectations</div>
          <div class="news-impact">$8.2B in Q4 capex alone. Plans to deploy $2.60 in capital for every $1 of 2026 revenue — far above analyst models. $14.9B total capex in 2025. Moody's projects negative FCF for 18+ months.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> InvestorPlace</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/03/02/3247636/0/en/CRWV-Alert-Hagens-Berman-Analyzes-CoreWeave-CRWV-452M-Q4-Loss-and-Soft-Guidance-Amid-Ongoing-Securities-Fraud-Litigation.html" target="_blank" class="news-item bad">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Mar 2–3, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag negative">Legal Risk</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">Securities Fraud Class Action Escalating</div>
          <div class="news-impact">Multiple law firms pursuing Masaitis v. CoreWeave. Allegations: concealed Denton TX construction delays, overstated scaling capabilities, understated single-supplier risk (Core Scientific named). Lead plaintiff deadline Mar 13.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> GlobeNewswire — Hagens Berman</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://investorplace.com/2026/03/coreweave-stock-crwv-buy-the-dip/" target="_blank" class="news-item bad">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Ongoing</span>
            <span class="impact-tag caution">Governance</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">Insider Selling Flagged by Analysts</div>
          <div class="news-impact">InvestorPlace flagged executives quietly unloading shares at a pace that raised red flags ahead of the Q4 earnings report. Combined with the 20% post-earnings stock drop, signals internal concern about near-term trajectory.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> InvestorPlace</span>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ===================== CORE SCIENTIFIC ===================== -->
    <div class="company-card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <div>
          <div class="ticker">CORZ</div>
          <div class="company-name">Core Scientific, Inc.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="risk-badge risk-high">&#9888; High</div>
      </div>

      <div class="toggle-bar">
        <div class="toggle-btn good-btn active" onclick="switchPanel(this,'corz-good','corz-bad')">
          <span class="icon">&#9650;</span> Good News <span class="count">5</span>
        </div>
        <div class="toggle-btn bad-btn" onclick="switchPanel(this,'corz-bad','corz-good')">
          <span class="icon">&#9660;</span> Bad News <span class="count">5</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="corz-good" class="news-panel active">

        <a href="https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/03/02/core-scientific-corz-q4-2025-earnings-transcript/" target="_blank" class="news-item good">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Mar 2, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag positive">Execution</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">350 MW Energized — On Track for 590 MW by Early 2027</div>
          <div class="news-impact">Past the halfway point on the CoreWeave contract. Denton TX campus delivering 67 billable MW across 3 buildings. Five AI factory sites representing $5B+ in total project investment and 5M+ labor hours.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> Motley Fool — Earnings Transcript</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20260302157124/en/Core-Scientific-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-Fiscal-Year-2025-Results" target="_blank" class="news-item good">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Mar 2, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag positive">Pivot Progress</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">Colocation Revenue Up 268% YoY</div>
          <div class="news-impact">Colocation revenue reached $31.3M in Q4, up from $8.5M a year earlier. Company expects a billing inflection point in coming months as additional megawatts come online and revenue ramps.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> BusinessWire — Earnings Release</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/03/02/core-scientific-corz-q4-2025-earnings-transcript/" target="_blank" class="news-item good">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Mar 2, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag positive">Diversification</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">500 MW Under Exclusivity With Investment-Grade Customer</div>
          <div class="news-impact">Management disclosed active negotiations for 500 MW of new colocation capacity with a large investment-grade counterparty. Would meaningfully reduce dependency on CoreWeave. Pricing trending higher.</div>
          <span class="source-link"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/></svg> Motley Fool — Earnings Transcript</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://investors.corescientific.com/news-events/press-releases/detail/127/core-scientific-announces-fourth-quarter-fiscal-year-2025-results" target="_blank" class="news-item good">
          <div class="news-meta">
            <span class="news-date">Mar 2, 2026</span>
            <span class="impact-tag positive">Liquidity</span>
          </div>
          <div class="news-title">$533M Liquidity + 1.5 GW Pipeline</div>
          <div class="news-impact">Year-end liquidity of $533.4M ($311M cash + $222M bitcoin). Up to $4B in potential project-based financing tied to CoreWeave contract. New sites in Hunt County TX (~430 MW), Dalton GA, and Pecos TX (~300 MW).</div>
